                  <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                      <seg type="rubrication">
                        <desc>In the Psalms of David, <locus target="#ms_i1.1" facs="005">fol. ms_i1.1</locus>, the scribe has placed a line of alternating red and black dots after every tenth Psalm.
                          On these same folios someone has sewn red yarn into the upper fore edge</desc>
                      </seg>
                      <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#80r #80v" facs="084 085">fols. 80r, 80v</locus> <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3</span></ref></desc>
