                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus from="ir" to="vv" facs="001">Fols ir–vv</locus> Excerpt from the <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3178Deggwa">Dǝggʷā</title> chant for the cross,
                              Gabriel, Mary, Palm Sunday (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆሣዕና፡</foreign>) Michael and John the Baptist</desc>
                              <notatedMusic><desc>with musical notations</desc></notatedMusic>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#94v" facs="099">Fol. 94v</locus>
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩፡</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#21v #41v #67r #75v #83r">folss. 21v, 41v, 67r, 75v, 83r, </locus>, etc.);
                          and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#17v">17v, </locus>, line 3, ),
                          and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#34v">34v, </locus>, line 10 and <locus target="#38r">38r</locus>, line 14)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the
                          codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>The general condition of the vellum is moderately dirty but relatively unworn</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#iv #94r">Fols. iv, 94r</locus> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
